 Veteran Broadcaster Larry King Larry King, giant of American broadcasting, has died at the age of 87 weeks after testing positive to Coronavirus. He died on Saturday at the Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in the city, according to Ora Media, a production company he co-founded. During his six-decade career, which included 25 years hosting his own CNN programme, King interviewed many famous political leaders, celebrities and sports people. Larry King, is said to have faced several health problems in recent years, including heart attacks. King, whose career spans over 60 years, has won multiple accolades, including two Peabody Awards and an Emmy.